               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>
                           <measure unit="leaf">iv + 66 </measure>
                           <measure unit="quire">Protection quire + 7</measure>
                           <dimensions type="outer" unit="mm">
                              <height>143</height>
                              <width>125</width>
                              <depth>47</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <collation>
                          <note>Quire descriptions: quires 1–3, 5–7 balanced; quire 4 unbalanced. Navigation systems: 1) crimson yarn sewn into corners of <locus target="#1 #13 #34 #54 #65" facs="005 017 038 058 069">folss. 1, 13, 34, 54, 65, </locus> to mark the location of miniatures;  2) various colored string sewn into corners of <locus target="#6 #16 #58" facs="010 020 062">6, 16, 58</locus> to mark content divisions.</note>
                          <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1" n="a">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">5</dim>
                                 <locus from="i" to="iv" facs="001">Fols i–iv, </locus>
                                 <locus target="#1" facs="005">Fol. 1</locus>
                                 <note>The protection quire construction is secondary. A single folio has been stitched to the back of the quire.</note>
                              Protection Quire:
                              5 added
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q2" n="1">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="2" to="9" facs="006">Fols 2–9</locus>
                                 <note>Quire 1's construction is secondary. The quire has been stitched together at three points in a round stitch (one that goes in one side of the quire about a half centimeter from the gutter fold and comes out the other side) at three points, head, middle and foot of the spine edge, thus making it impossible to verify the inner construction of the quire. </note>
                              Quire 1
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q3" n="2">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">8</dim>
                                 <locus from="10" to="17" facs="014">Fols 10–17</locus>
                                 <note>Quire 2's construction is secondary. The quire has been stitched together at two points in a round stitch at two points, middle and foot of the spine edge, thus making it impossible to verify the inner construction of the quire. Thus, the image is imprecise, e.g., <locus target="#14 #15" facs="018 019">fols. 14, 15</locus> are one sheet.</note>
                              Quire 2
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q4" n="3">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">10</dim>
                                 <locus from="18" to="27" facs="022">Fols 18–27</locus>
                                 <note>Quire 3's construction is secondary if not tertiary. There is evidence of not one but two non-original gathering strategies:  1) <locus from="18" to="24" facs="022">fols 18–24, </locus> have three small reinforcement strips sewn around them, suggesting a first repair; 2) The current full quire includes the folio constituted by <locus from="18" to="24" facs="022">18–24</locus>. The entire folio has been stitched together at three points in a round stitch at three points, head, middle and foot of the spine edge, thus making it impossible to verify the inner construction of the quire. The image is imprecise.</note>
                              Quire 3
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q5" n="4">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">7</dim>
                                 <locus from="28" to="34" facs="032">Fols 28–34</locus>
                                 <note>Quire 4's construction is secondary. The quire has been stitched together at three points in a round stitch at three points, head, middle and foot of the spine edge, thus making it impossible to verify the inner construction of the quire. Thus, the image may be imprecise.</note>
                              Quire 4:
                              1 added
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q6" n="5">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">6</dim>
                                 <locus from="35" to="40" facs="039">Fols 35–40</locus>
                              Quire 5
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q7" n="6">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">14</dim>
                                 <locus from="41" to="54" facs="045">Fols 41–54</locus>
                              Quire 6
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q8" n="7">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">12</dim>
                                 <locus from="55" to="66" facs="059">Fols 55–66</locus>
                              Quire 7
                            </item>
                          </list>
                        </collation>
